		<article class="article-half-list"><div class="in">
				<h1>More about project</h1>
			<div class="desc-half-list">
				<p>H1.cz decided to bring more detailed and faster data to its employees,
				elevating its practise of data-driven operational management.
				While migrating their reporting and project management systems,
				the agency needed to hold on to its old know-how,
				as well as the data itself being exported from their older systems.
				In the world of agency business, the level of speed and amount of detail
				available to employees is a crucial determining factor between profit and loss.
				Keeping this in mind, all employees constantly require information about things
				like KPIs, consultants, billed time, budgets, etc.
				While the new CRM implementation was taking longer than expected,
				management had only partial information about their business.

				</p>

					<p>
					The result was that they were unable to distinguish which projects
						and people were generating <STRONG>profits</STRONG> or <STRONG>losses</STRONG>, and <STRONG>when</STRONG>.
						It became increasingly difficult to implement the organization’s
						operational management properly. To overcome all this, H1.cz management realized
						that they needed a <STRONG>universal</STRONG> reporting tool which would allow an easy access to both
						their old and new data. This allowed H1.cz connections to things like:
						their old and new <STRONG>CRM</STRONG> simultaneously, specialized tools for <STRONG>advertisement</STRONG> management,
						<STRONG>analytics</STRONG> as well as <STRONG>time-tracking</STRONG> tools such as Toggl, <STRONG>accounting</STRONG>, etc.
						Seamlessly integrating data sources during ongoing scheduling presented a big challenge,
						leading them to make Keboola Connection their ultimate choice.

					</p>
				</div>
			</div></article>

